E.J.B. for Entreprise Java Beans are java Classes that implement at least two interfaces or with an annotation (as of E.J.B. 3.0 specification and later ).
They can be :
  Session beans meaning that can be called on demand 
  Message-driven beans meaning that they called when a J.M.S. messsage goes in a J.M.S. queue.
 Session beans can be either :
  Stateless beans : beans that have no data (attributs).
  Stateful beans : beans that do.Their data holds invocation things.One per call of bean.
  Singleton
JNDI : EJB, a Datasource or a JMS Queue - string map. string is usually like "{resourceType}/{resourceName}"
